
Computational Advertising is a relatively new discipline within Computer Science that deals with algorithms of presenting the best advertisement displayed to a person, typically through an Internet browser.Computation Advertising, Yahoo Research

== Research and Academic Courses ==

Computational Advertising is being taught at major universities: Stanford University,MS&E 239: Introduction to Computational Advertising, Stanford University University of California,Introduction to Computational Advertising, University of California among others.
Major technology corporations conduct applied research in this new discipline: Microsoft,Computational Advertising and Recommendation, Microsoft Research Yahoo,Computational Advertising, Andrei Broder and Vanja Josifovski, Yahoo Research among others.

== History ==

In 2009 NISS, National Institute of Statistical Sciences held a workshop on Computational Advertising.NISS Affiliates Workshop on Computational Advertising

